Light weaponry is oft looked down upon by the masses as the tools of cowards and weaklings. A dagger cannot put fear in an opponent like a glistening long sword. At least, not until a group of thieves, assassins and other nightwalkers known as the Guild of the Red Moon started carrying light weaponry that could punch through plate smooth as silk and quietly as a whisper. The Sureforged, as they are now known, are a must have commodity for any respectable adventurer who prefers his slaughter silent.

Refined and pressed into a liquid, this belladonna extract is extremely potent compared to the raw herb.

You can easy use this in small doses and still have a more effective means than chewing a leave.

A friendly cat who "fights" with Boulderdash for dominance of their home..
A cheery spotted dog with a red bandana around his neck.

Value.value: *his tongue lolls out of his mouth as he expects attention*

value.0: An energetic half-elven girl who looks to be in her late teens. She has a quick smile and is always eager to play some music.

A fine stringed instrument, a lute is very mobile, and as such, a favorite of traveling minstrels everywhere.  It has a pleasing sound, as the strings musical vibrations echo in the hollow wooden chamber and reverberate.

Value.value: Hello! I came to live with my sister because she's not stuffy like Marcus.
Have you seen Boulderdash around? He's always breaking things! He's worse than the cat!
I broke a plate and Jilly had an anxiety attack. She must have worked for mean people in Southport before she came here.
Want to hear a song? I can play all kinds of instruments!

value.0: This human woman appears to be quite the diligent worker! If a bit neurotic at times. Jilly, as Gabria calls her, is a former resident of Southport who came to Moonpier looking for work after the Swords of the South took over the southern city. She seems a bit anxious at times, but she's quite friendly when she's not freaking out about accidents and spills.

Value.value: *spares a brief smile, but focuses on her work*
*pauses to stare anxiously at a speck of dirt on the fine marble floors, and takes a deep breath*

value.0: This human woman is almost always humming as she goes about her work in the kitchen. She loves cooking, and ensures the family she serves never goes hungry - even when they might stay up into all hours of the night and forget that they need to eat.

Value.value: *spares a brief smile, but focuses on her work*
*pauses to stare anxiously at a speck of dirt on the fine marble floors, and takes a deep breath*

value.0: Nylan is a local gossip, but she is known to be dedicated to her kids above all else. And she has a whole litter of them.
Used as a toy for children for time on end, baby dolls are often cute.  This is the non-wetting kind, however.

Value.value: Mmm... A sweetberry. Thank you. This will make them happy. *smiles and gives you some gold*
Mm, hello. *she smiles, gazing at you with piercing eyes* My children are clamoring for sweets. Perhaps you can find some sweetberries for them, hm? I'll pay you for any you bring.

value.0: One of the Kieran boys, Nolan is most known for being extremely playful, but a touch too competitive. Much to his mother's chagrin, he spends a lot of his time in his hybrid form.

Value.value: *growls with frustration* Haldien won't race meeee!

value.0: One of the Kieran boys, Haldien is best known for sneaking around and eavesdropping. He gets into plenty of trouble, but he's still quite beloved around town.

Value.value: I'm being good. *nods sagely* No racing down the bridge. It's dangerous, momma says.

value.0: One of the Kieran girls, Minerva is best known for actually being the well-behaved one of the bunch. She still gets into some trouble, but she loves books so much that they keep her attention long enough for her to miss most of the antics her brothers get up to.
A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!

Value.value: *glances up from her book to examine you, but then just looks back down to continue reading*

value.0: One of the Kieran girls, Felina is the oldest of the kids. She usually ends up chasing after her rowdy brothers, but she prefers to watch people as they go about their daily lives. She finds people fascinating, and perhaps stares a little too much. She's still quite loved, though. The people of Moonpier are quite used to the Kieran family peculiarities.

A small shrine dedicated to Eilistraee.

"Be always kind, save in battle with evil. Encourage happiness everywhere. Learn and teach new songs, dances, and the flowing dance of skilled sword work. Promote harmony between the races. Befriend strangers, shelter those without homes, and feed the hungry. Repay rudeness with kindness. Repay violence with swift violence so that those that cause it are swiftly dealt with. Aid drow in distress, and give them the Lady's message: 'A rightful place awaits you in the Realms Above, in the Land of the Great Light. Come in peace and live beneath the sun again where trees and flowers grow.' "

A small shrine dedicated to Mystra.

"Love magic for itself. Do not treat it just as a weapon to reshape the world to your will. True wisdom is knowing when not to use magic. Strive to use magic less as your powers develop, for often the threat or promise of its use outstrips its actual performance. Magic is Art, the Gift of the Lady, and those who wield it are privileged in the extreme. Conduct yourself humbly, not proudly, while being mindful of this. Use the Art deftly and efficiently, not carelessly and recklessly. Seek always to learn and create new magic."
